<p>

This parish includes the villages of Vale das Fontes, Nuzedo de Baixo and Minas. These villages belong to the so-called <it>terra quente</it>, or hot land. <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
Olive oil</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../961/32961.xml">
wine</link> are the main agricultural produce.</p>
<p>

The population in 2007 was 432.</p>
<p>

The Tuela river, a tributary of the Tua river, crosses this territory throughout deep, fertile and pleasant valleys.</p>
